(First Circuit-Hamilton Co., O., Circuit Court Jan. Term, 1897.) Before Day, Price and Norris, JJ.

(The judges of the Third Circuit sitting in the First Circuit.)

JNO. KRAUSE v. AMANDA E. STICHTENOTH et al. Overruling Demurrer with leave to answer, is. not final order to which error will lie. Dat, J.

The ruling of the court of commón pleas, sustaining the demurrer to the petition in this case, and granting leave to amend the pleading in ten days, is not a final order to which error will lie.

The petition in error is dismissed.
